修改callback有点不好
1，callback是很早之前就开放给客户端使用了，现在改为只能执行一次，对低版本升级兼容有影响
2，重复多次只有callback异常才会发生，我建议的是迭代的时候标记key，然后执行exception的时候再去removekey，这样也解决了并发问题，对原有的callback也没有影响。

Modifying the callback is a bit of a bad thing. 
1. Callback was opened to the client a long time ago, but now it can only be executed once, which will affect the compatibility of lower version upgrade. 
2. Only the callback exception will occur if the callback is repeated several times. What I suggest is to mark the key during iteration and then removekey when the exception is executed, which also solves the concurrency problem and has no effect on the original callback.

public static void scanExpiredRequest() {
        Iterator<Map.Entry<String, RequestResponseFuture>> it = requestFutureTable.entrySet().iterator();
        Set<String> expiredKeys = new HashSet<String>()
        while (it.hasNext()) {
            Map.Entry<String, RequestResponseFuture> next = it.next();
            RequestResponseFuture rep = next.getValue();

            if (rep.isTimeout()) {
                expiredKeys .add(next.getKey());
            }
        }
        for(String expiredKey : expiredKeys){
                RequestResponseFuture rf = requestFutureTable.remove(expiredKey);
                if(rf != null){
                        try {
                                Throwable cause = new RequestTimeoutException(ClientErrorCode.REQUEST_TIMEOUT_EXCEPTION, "request timeout, no reply message.");
                                rf.setCause(cause);
                                rf.executeRequestCallback();
                        } catch (Throwable e) {
                            log.warn("scanResponseTable, operationComplete Exception", e);
                        }
                }
        }
    }




